.%20Matthews%20II%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20own%20a%20home%20and%20know%20it's%20the%20right%20lifestyle%20choice%20for%20me%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20the%20best%20investment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20ran%20the%20numbers%2C%20and%20I%20could%20be%20earning%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20more%20by%20investing%20in%20the%20market.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20trick%20for%20renters%20is%3A%20You%20have%20to%20invest%20the%20money%20you'd%20otherwise%20spend%20on%20home%20maintenance.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20for%20owning%20a%20home%20is%20a%20simple%20one%3A%20You%20put%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-much-down-payment-for-a-house%5C%22%3Edown%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20your%20initial%20investment%2C%20take%20out%20a%20mortgage%2C%20and%20over%20time%2C%20you%20build%20equity%20as%20the%20value%20of%20the%20home%20grows.%20Should%20you%20decide%20to%20sell%2C%20you%20may%20make%20a%20profit.%20Or%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%2C%20you%20now%20have%20an%20asset%20to%20pass%20down%20to%20a%20family%20member%20or%20a%20place%20you%20can%20rent%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20in%20the%20homeownership%20camp%20argue%20that%20since%20you%20need%20a%20place%20to%20live%2C%20it%20makes%20more%20sense%20to%20pay%20a%20set%20cost%20for%20a%20defined%20period%20of%20time%20and%20gain%20equity%20out%20of%20the%20arrangement%20rather%20than%20paying%20rent%20indefinitely.%20It%20can%20also%20be%20argued%20that%20homeowners%20have%20the%20advantage%20of%20borrowing%20against%20the%20equity%20in%20their%20home%20as%20another%20important%20benefit.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20a%20financial%20professional%20and%20homeowner%20myself%2C%20I%20still%20see%20renting%20as%20a%20more%20conducive%20and%20efficient%20option%20for%20investing%20and%20building%20wealth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20the%20math%20can%20favor%20renters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20bought%20our%20home%2C%20priced%20at%20%24400%2C000%2C%20in%20August%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20say%20over%20the%20next%2030%20years%20that%20the%20price%20of%20the%20home%20appreciates%20at%20current%20historical%20rates%20of%20about%204%25.%20That%20means%20that%20in%20year%2030%2C%20the%20house%20would%20be%20worth%20%241.3%20million%20for%20a%20profit%20of%20%24900%2C000.%20This%20is%20how%20most%20homeowners%20calculate%20their%20gains%20on%20a%20home%20%E2%80%94%20by%20subtracting%20the%20value%20of%20the%20home%20when%20they%20purchased%20and%20the%20value%20when%20they%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20doing%20this%20calculation%20is%20incorrect.%20It%20doesn't%20take%20into%20account%20all%20of%20the%20costs%20of%20owning%20the%20home%2C%20including%20the%20interest%20paid%20during%20the%20life%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%3Emortgage%20loan%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20potential%20homeowners%20underestimate%20the%20costs%20of%20ongoing%20upkeep%20and%20repairs.%20A%20good%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%20to%20maintain%20a%20cash%20reserve%20equal%20to%201%25%20of%20your%20home's%20price%20for%20unexpected%20bills%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Joel%20Ohman%2C%20a%20financial%20planner%20and%20CEO%20of%20Clearsurance.com.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20low%20estimate%20for%20homeowners%20can%20sometimes%20be%20hidden%20and%20seen%20as%20hobbies%20instead%20of%20expenses%20that%20should%20be%20accounted%20for.%20%26quot%3BMost%20people%20who%20invest%20time%20and%20money%20into%20landscaping%20don't%20think%20of%20it%20as%20a%20homeownership%20cost%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jeffrey%20Zhou%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20lending%20company%20Fig%20Loans.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccounting%20for%20the%20true%20cost%20of%20homeownership%20in%20my%20situation%20would%20include%20the%20following%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%24562%2C400%20is%20the%20total%20cost%20of%20all%20principal%2C%20interest%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fpmi-private-mortgage-insurance%5C%22%3Emortgage%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20loan%20costs%2C%20not%20the%20%24400%2C000%20price%20of%20the%20home%20when%20we%20purchased%20it%20according%20to%20our%20actual%20loan%20documents%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%24120%2C000%20would%20be%20the%20total%20annual%20maintenance%20expense%20over%2030%20years%20using%20Oshman's%20rule%20of%20thumb%2C%20not%20including%20large%20expenses%2C%20like%20HVAC%20or%20any%20remodeling%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20two%20expenses%20alone%20add%20up%20to%20%24682%2C400%2C%20making%20our%20total%20profit%20over%2030%20years%20%24617%2C000.%20Using%20the%20amounts%20saved%2C%20let's%20look%20at%20how%20a%20renter%20would%20fare%20if%20the%20upfront%20costs%20and%20maintenance%20were%20invested%20using%20historical%20data%20for%20the%20past%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20spent%20a%20total%20of%20%2441%2C000%20between%20closing%20costs%20and%20the%20down%20payment.%20If%20we%20invested%20%2441%2C000%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20in%20the%20first%20year%20and%20added%20what%20would%20have%20been%20an%20annual%20maintenance%20cost%20of%20%244%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20we%20could%20have%20%242%2C045%2C485%20in%2030%20years%20with%20%241%2C844%2C485%20in%20total%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20situation%2C%20the%20renter%20would%20have%20a%20higher%20return%20on%20investment%2C%20with%20%241.8%20million%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20homeowner%2C%20with%20just%20%24617%2C000.%20Even%20though%20the%20homeowner's%20payment%20stops%20once%20the%20mortgage%20is%20paid%2C%20the%20return%20on%20investment%20from%20just%20the%20down%20payment%20and%20maintenance%20expense%20favors%20the%20renter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20arguments%20for%20and%20against%20homeownership%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3EThe%20renter%20is%20subject%20to%20rising%20costs%20indefinitely%3B%20the%20homeowner%20has%20one%20fixed%20cost%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20true%2C%20but%20even%20with%20rising%20rent%20each%20year%2C%20it%20does%20not%20impact%20the%20initial%20down%20payment%20or%20maintenance%20costs%20that%20the%20renter%20would%20experience.%20Also%2C%20the%20renter%20also%20has%20the%20ability%20to%20relocate%20to%20cheaper%20areas%20to%20offset%20those%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%2030%20years%2C%20the%20homeowner%20will%20not%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20housing%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20renter%20will%20still%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20housing%20indefinitely%2C%20in%20this%20scenario%20the%20renter%20still%20has%20nearly%20three%20times%20more%20money%20at%20year%2030%20than%20the%20homeowner.%20Also%2C%20the%20homeowner%20still%20pays%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fproperty-tax-by-state%5C%22%3Eproperty%20taxes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20may%20increase%20over%20time%2C%20and%20still%20has%20to%20contend%20with%20annual%20maintenance.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20about%20the%20tax%20benefits%3F%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20benefits%20of%20owning%20a%20home%20was%20the%20ability%20to%20deduct%20the%20interest%20on%20a%20mortgage.%20Deducting%20this%20cost%20would%20increase%20homeowners'%20return%20on%20investment%2C%20but%20the%20Tax%20Cuts%20and%20Jobs%20Act%20of%202017%20nullified%20most%20of%20this%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20filers%20now%20just%20use%20the%20standard%20deduction%20rather%20than%20itemizing.%20When%20you%20have%20a%20mortgage%2C%20the%20interest%20is%20deductible%20as%20an%20itemized%20deduction.%20However%2C%20since%20most%20people%20use%20the%20standard%20deduction%20now%2C%20the%20tax%20benefits%20of%20a%20mortgage%20are%20largely%20lost%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Steven%20Gilbert%2C%20a%20financial%20planner%20and%20founder%20of%20Gilbert%20Wealth.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20primary%20home%20does%20not%20have%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20an%20investment.%20Just%20like%20a%20car%2C%20furniture%2C%20and%20other%20regular%20purchases%2C%20your%20home%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20lifestyle%20purchase%20that%20just%20so%20happens%20to%20appreciate%20in%20value%20depending%20on%20your%20market.%20Ohman%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20renting%20saves%20money%20and%20reduces%20stress%20so%20you%20can%20accomplish%20your%20financial%20objectives%2C%20it%20may%20be%20the%20best%20way%20to%20build%20your%20net%20worth.%20The%20critical%20action%20for%20renters%20is%20to%20successfully%20invest%20the%20savings%20they%20would%20have%20spent%20on%20a%20home%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20know%20where%20to%20start%3F%20Consider%20a%20financial%20advisor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20orig